For use in sections

*   Further information: [WP:SUMMARYHATNOTE](/Wikipedia:SUMMARYHATNOTE)

" Main article: ... "

{{[Main](/Template:Main)}} is used to make [summary style](/Wikipedia:Summary_style) explicit, when used in a summary section for which there is also a separate article on the subject:

*   `{{Main|Main Article}}` →
    Main article: [Main Article](/Main_Article)
*   `{{Main|Main Article|Article2}}` →
    Main articles: [Main Article](/Main_Article) and [Article2](/Article2)
*   `{{Main list|Article1}}` →
    For a more comprehensive list, see Article1.
*   `{{Main category|Category name}}` →
    Main category: Category name

" Further information: ... "

{{[Further](/Template:Further)}} can supplement {{[Main](/Template:Main)}} in summary sections, or can indicate more details in nonsummary sections:

*   `{{Further|PAGE}}` →
    Further information: [PAGE](/PAGE)
*   `{{Further|PAGE1|PAGE2|PAGE3}}` →
    Further information: [PAGE1](/PAGE1), PAGE2, and PAGE3
*   `{{Further|topic=TOPIC|PAGE1|PAGE2|PAGE3}}` →
    Further information on TOPIC: [PAGE1](/PAGE1), PAGE2, and PAGE3
*   `{{Further2|[[PAGE1]], [[PAGE2]], and other text}}` →
    Further information: [PAGE1](/PAGE1), PAGE2, and other text
*   {{[Further ill](/Template:Further_ill)}} may be used to link to articles containing further information on a topic, where English Wikipedia does not yet have an article, but another language Wikipedia does.

" See also ... "

{{[See also](/Template:See_also)}} can be used at the head of a section.

*   `{{See also|TOPIC PAGE|OTHER TOPIC PAGE}}` →

Note: use only when OTHER TOPIC PAGE is related to current article and contains a self-explanatory parenthetical.

*   `{{See also2|[[OTHER TOPIC]]|[[OTHER TOPIC2]]|[[OTHER TOPIC3]] and other text}}` →
    See also: OTHER TOPIC, OTHER TOPIC2, and OTHER TOPIC3 and other text

Article or section transclusions

*   `{{Transcluding article|PAGE1|PAGE2|PAGE3...}}` (used when [transcluding](/Help:Transclusion) 1 or more entire articles into a target article) →
    Transcluding articles: [PAGE1](/PAGE1), PAGE2, and [...](/...)
*   `{{Transcluded section|PAGE}}` (used when [selectively transcluding a section](/Help:Transclusion) from one article into a section of the target article) →
    This section is [transcluded](/Help:Transclusion) from [PAGE](/PAGE). (edit | history)
*   `{{Transcluded section|PAGE|part=yes}}` (used when selectively transcluding a section into part of a section on the target page) →
